Dear Hiring Team,

It is with great interest that I submit my candidacy for the *Software Engineer - Full Stack* role with *Emergence AI*. I bring experience building backend services, frontend workflow tools, and production agent systems with *Python*, *FastAPI*, *React*, *TypeScript*, *PostgreSQL*, *Redis*, and *CI/CD*, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend and agentic systems that directly reflect *the technical depth this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I designed a multi-agent CRM orchestration system using *LangGraph*, *LangChain*, and *FastAPI* that routes requests to 40+ specialized sub-agents with secure access control and production *RESTful* and *event-driven APIs*. I also built *test automation* and regression suites across backend APIs, *frontend components*, and agent workflows by replaying OpenTelemetry traces in *GitHub Actions CI/CD* to validate *integration tests*, *end-to-end test scenarios*, and *automated testing frameworks* before *production deployment*. To support daily operations, I built a *React* Flow and *TypeScript* workflow UI for agent monitoring and workflow visualization, plus a *FastMCP* server exposing 160+ backend actions with *logging, tracing, and performance monitoring* and multi-tenant *observability dashboards*. I also built *LlamaIndex*-powered RAG agents with OpenAI embeddings and *Pgvector* to answer product questions and generate ready-to-run *REST* API examples for internal development. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Springboot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis* that handled file operations across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO* via expiring signed URLs. I also optimized *SQL* workloads in *PostgreSQL* with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, exposed the results through *React* visualizations for business stakeholders, and orchestrated long-running, event-driven jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, reducing *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improving error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions. Together, these roles have prepared me to contribute meaningfully to the team's core engineering responsibilities while owning features end-to-end.

Emergence’s focus on *making mission-critical autonomy possible* resonates strongly with the way I like to build: verified, measurable, and reliable. Your emphasis on *verified autonomy* and *performance, safety, and reliability* aligns with the testing and instrumentation work I have already been doing across agent workflows, backend APIs, and production infrastructure. I would be excited to bring that mindset to *this team and its mission*, especially where your platform needs trustworthy execution, strong observability, and careful iteration under senior engineering guidance.

I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my background can help advance *making mission-critical autonomy possible* for *Emergence AI*. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

